headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 34 points and Jalen Duren's dunk in the final minute punctuated a late 10-2 run, helping the Detroit Pistons to a 113-106 win over the Charlotte Hornets on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Bojan Bogdanovic and Jalen Duren help rally Pistons to a 113-106 win over the Hornets

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 38 points and the Western Conference-leading Minnesota Timberwolves avoided their first three-game skid of the season, beating the Washington Wizards 118-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 38 as Timberwolves return to form, beat Wizards 118-107

headlines.description: — The Memphis Grizzlies were wildly short-handed. And the Miami Heat still couldn't handle them.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Grizzlies spoil Terry Rozier’s Miami debut and hand Heat 4th straight loss, 105-96

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 33 points and Jerami Grant added 21 as the Portland Trail Blazers rallied to beat the Houston Rockets 137-131 in overtime on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anfernee Simons scores 33 points as Trail Blazers rally to beat Rockets 137-131 in overtime

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo made sure the Milwaukee Bucks delivered a win the night after their coach was fired.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo gets triple-double as Bucks beat Cavs 126-116 in 1st game since Griffin was fired

headlines.description: — Devin Booker has seen some chippy games between his Phoenix Suns and Luka Doncic's Dallas Mavericks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 46 as Suns beat Mavs 132-109 for 7th consecutive win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Oklahoma City did not lose sight of its objective even as the focus was squarely on the battle between San Antonio’s Victor Wembanyama and fellow rookie Chet Holmgren.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander helps Thunder overcome Wembanyama, Spurs, to win 4th straight 140-114

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — With several of his players overcome by emotions just moments before tip-off after celebrating the assistant coach they dearly miss, Steve Kerr stuck to his message: “Try to lose yourself in the game.”
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors return to game action after assistant coach's death last week, beat Hawks 134-112
